text:
I love how WinWin describes his relationship with Taeil - a cat and his owner. It is exactly like that, like me and my cat.

Also, I am loving his development here. Nothing is wrong with him being the guy who was not used to affection. But I also like how he builds his confidence. 

It seems like some fans forget that when he first debuted in NCT, he was newish in SM and also came from China - adding to the pressure. Fans knew him as the guy who spoke little Korean at first in NCT Life, appeared in that teaser and then in Without You MV. In addition, he was relatively on the younger sides. He was not like Yuta, who had been introduced as rookies for a while and spoke Korean relatively fluently, and was on the older side. 

So, WinWin had to navigate all that when he debuted. Then, he was often showered with attention by the members (while he was probably still getting used to be the centre of attention).

So ofc the dynamics b/w WinWin in WayV and him in 127/U tends to be different. In WayV, he shares more commonalities with the members, being foreigners in Korea and sharing language with the majority. He is also in the middle, age wise. 

I am not trying to overanalyse him or his relationship with other members, but to show a bit more background without saying he was closer to a specific group (bcs how would I know?).

Whether he returned to 127 or not, I think it is more important for WinWin to get a say in that.

text:
This might sound strange as this episode is so exciting and funny... But, I found myself crying in the middle of this episode. I can see that 127 squad definitely missed and longed for Winwin and his presence, they've been together in the group for so long and built great memories not knowing that things would turn 360 degress for both the members especially Winwin. I remember when Taeil said that when they are eating, Winwin secretly paid for the bill. The way that it feels like it's his way of saying goodbye.

I'm so glad that Winwin is doing great with WayV, the way that they treat and care for each other like family is so heartwarming. It's just at some point you'll miss him with 127, and the turning of events will really make you sad. I'm glad NCT 2020 happened 💚

Supporting 23 members all the way ♡

Edit: I'm not saying that Sicheng isn't part of 127 anymore. I'm sorry if I made confusion. Take care!

text: For all those people that are saying “we want Winwin back in NCT 127” probably don’t even keep up with WAYV. Winwin is so happy in WAYV and it is evident. He is confident and adores his brothers, especially loves taking care of his younger brothers. He has mentioned countless times that he can be himself with his WAYV members and that he sees them as his family. He even spent over $1,000 dollars on a ring for Lucas to represent their friendship and was given a bracelet with the words “Be Brave” given to him by Hendery which was emotional. In WAYV he is free to express himself and he gets a lot more exposure, but most of all he is happy because he’s with his family. In my opinion WAYV was the best thing that happened for both Ten and Winwin. I hope you guys can start paying attention to WAYV after NCT 2020 :)
